<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36117b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36117b">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36117b"> 117(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> payable on Strong-/bow&apos;s tomb</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">There was an old custom in bygone times of making the principal sums in bonds <mark>payable &ldquo;on Strongbow&apos;s tomb,&rdquo;</mark> recalling the analogous Limerick custom of payments &ldquo;on the nail,&rdquo; the said &ldquo;nail&rdquo; being a prominent public stone. <small> Dublin Corporation. <a name="DCOG" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#DCOG"><cite title="source">The Official Guide to the City of Dublin</cite></a> (published annually) 68</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c09072a" href="c09all.htm#c09072a">VI.C.09:072(a)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
